is a temporary employment authorization for f-1 international students who are currently pursuing a program of study at sjsu and want to gain practical training in their major field of study. cpt may be authorized for paid or unpaid employment.for cpt authorization and application periods, eligibility, and required documents (including job offer letter specifications), please check the issscpt webpageand theircpt tutorial [pdf].at coe, the application process includes meeting any additional departmental requirements for eligibility, being aware of cpt departmental policy, and obtaining approval by your major or program department.note: the application process has changed as of july 2021.overview of the cpt application process at coe:after reviewing your department's website for further details, please reach out to theundergraduate or graduate departmental contacts for cptif you have any questions.post-completion opt is a temporary employment authorization issued by uscis that may be used (1) after the completion of a degree program, or (2) after completion of all course requirements other than a thesis, project or comprehensive final exam. the work students pursue while on post-completion opt must be directly related to their major field of study.post-completion opt is generally issued for a duration of 12 months, but may be for less time if the student has previously applied and been granted pre-completion opt.more information on theprocess for post-optis available on the isss website, along with a detailedtutorial [pdf].pre-completion opt is another type of work authorization that occurs prior to students' degree completion and before the program end date stated on the i-20. learn more about theeligibility and process for pre-opton the isss website.the academic advisor will complete part of your opt application form before you submit that to isss. each department may have a different process for submission and required documents to attach. please check their website and, if you still have questions,reach out to the departmental contact for opt.if you are unsure which opt option to pursue,make an appointment with an isss advisorto discuss your options given your case.e-form guide (students)essc cpt workshopsisss formsisss workshopsmonday through friday, during business hours (closed weekends and holidays)visit office: virtually or in person at eng 116undergraduate:success-engineering@sjsu.edugraduate:graduate-engineering@sjsu.eduappointments with advisors:spartan connectphone: 408-924-3990all online courses at sjsu are delivered throughcanvas.monday through friday (except weekends and holidays), hours depending on location.: see our calendar forvirtual/drop-in hours: engineering 1st floor eng 116monday through friday8:30 a.m. to 12:00 noon1:00 p.m. to 4:30 p.m.(closed for lunch daily 12:00 - 1:00)in-person drop-in calendarsan jos state universityone washington square,san jos, ca 95192-0220